abstract: >-
  This dataset contains the complete validation results for EVAOnline, 
  an open-source Kalman fusion system for reference evapotranspiration (ETo) 
  estimation in Brazil. The dataset includes daily ETo values from four sources:
  (1) Xavier et al. reference data (1961-2024), (2) NASA POWER reanalysis,
  (3) Open-Meteo Archive, and (4) EVAOnline Kalman fusion results.
  Data covers 17 Brazilian cities in the MATOPIBA region (2017-2024),
  totaling over 186,000 daily observations. EVAOnline demonstrates superior
  performance with Mean Absolute Error of 0.48 mm/day and near-zero bias (0.6%),
  compared to NASA POWER (MAE=1.09 mm/day, PBIAS=23.2%) and Open-Meteo
  (MAE=0.67 mm/day, PBIAS=8.8%). The repository includes raw data, validation
  scripts, statistical analyses, and reproducible Jupyter notebooks.
